snippet.textDisplay:
To all those people saying “AJ was just running”:
First of all, you’re just casuals, because boxing is a sport of strategy and adaptation. AJ did just that, he outboxed Ruiz exploiting his opponent’s weaknesses. If you think a fight is just standing face to face and trading punches, you clearly don’t know much about boxing and, secondly, you’re not going to last very long as a fighter that way.
AJ’s tactic was to remain light on the feet, keep moving, mantaining distance with a precise jab. If you believe that that’s easy means you don’t know shit about being 12 rounds in a boxing ring. AJ’s conditioning was extraordinary, how he kept moving, switching things up, man, that’s a world class fighter right there.
Joshua definetly deserves to be Heavyweight champion!

(Don’t get me wrong, Ruiz is also an amazing fighter, but he got outsmarted this time.
Now I would love to see AJ fight Wilder or Fury in the near future)

snippet.textDisplay: If you know Boxing, you knew how dangerous Ruiz is. Fights at the top aren't about who does what right, its about who does what wrong. The Joshua who beat Breazeale, was always a nightmare match up for Ruiz, hands high, ram rod jab. I believed he'd win the rematch if he came in lighter, and he never disappointed. Its funny how the people annoyed at his tactics, all love Fury. Joshua deserves every success he gets, and even if he loses his next 10 fights, he's still a champion of life.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm not really a fan of this era of boxing, when a man can turn up to a fight in the condition that ruiz did it speaks volumes of his commitment or LACK of it. Having said that I think everyone is blowing this victory way out of proportion, AJ had an auro of vulnerability the whole fight and I'm not sure the way he won was the only style that could be used to beat ruiz, if a Fat guy had bullied and beat me up like ruiz did to AJ I'm not so sure I'd be as gassed over a klitschko type win, when Lewis got sparked in 5 by Rahman he put him to sleep in 4 in the rematch, for me that's the best way to exorcise your demons, everyone will be onto AJ now because they know what his weaknesses are but atleast it should make the division more exciting, let's hope hearn has better competition than pulev as I don't want to see that fight.
This era now seems more about who has the largest fan base that who is really the best😕
